  description={`AI WhatsApp for UK demolition contractors. Responds to building photos, demolition tenders, and emergency dangerous structure messages while you run the plant. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
  canonicalUrl="/demolition-contractors/ai-whatsapp/"
  channelName="AI WhatsApp"
  tradeName="Demolition Contractor"
  tradeNamePlural="Demolition Contractors"
  tradeSlug="demolition-contractors"
  headline="AI WhatsApp for UK Demolition Contractor Companies"
  accentWord="Demolition"
  subhead="A developer WhatsApps at 11am with six photos — a disused 1950s brick-and-concrete social club in Headington. The photos show the front elevation with boarded windows, the rear with a flat-roof kitchen extension, an interior showing a suspended ceiling void and commercial bar fit-out, and the yard with concrete hardstanding and a brick boundary wall. His message: 'This social club needs demolishing. 2 storeys, about 600 sqm footprint. Brick walls, concrete floor slabs, flat roofs. Still has the full bar and kitchen fit-out inside — stainless steel counters, commercial equipment, the lot. Need soft strip first then full demolition. Site needs clearing to formation for housing. My programme has piling starting in 10 weeks. R&D asbestos survey done — ACMs found in the floor tiles and pipe lagging. Can you tender? Need prices by next Wednesday.' You are on a demolition site in Witney — supervising a 360 excavator with a concrete pulveriser attached, systematically crunching through reinforced concrete beams. The exclusion zone is active, the banksman managing lorry movements. Your phone is in the site office portakabin. Without AI WhatsApp, the social club tender sits until the afternoon tea break. With it, the AI responds instantly, asks about vehicle access width, whether the boundary wall is retained, and the required formation level, and your lead — 1950s social club, Headington, 600 sqm, two-storey, brick/concrete, full bar and kitchen soft strip, ACMs identified, housing development, ten-week programme, prices by Wednesday — is captured with six photos attached."
  scenario="It is Saturday evening. A commercial landlord in Bicester owns a derelict row of three single-storey retail units with a shared concrete yard and underground drainage. The units have been vacant for four years. Vandals have stripped the copper and smashed the shopfronts. The landlord wants all three units demolished, the yard concrete broken out, the underground drainage grubbed up, and the site cleared and levelled for sale as a development plot. He WhatsApps three demolition firms: 'Hi — I own 3 derelict shop units in Bicester. Single storey, steel frame with blockwork infill, flat roofs. About 250 sqm total. They are in bad shape — vandalised, stripped. Need everything demolished and cleared including the yard concrete and underground drainage. Want the site clean for sale. What would you charge? No rush on the programme but I want to crack on soon.' Without AI WhatsApp, you see the message Sunday evening. One firm replied Saturday with a rough price range. With AI WhatsApp, the response arrives within seconds, asks about the roof material, whether the flat roofs might contain asbestos, and the site access for plant. He confirms profiled metal roofs with no known asbestos. Monday you open the lead: three derelict retail units, Bicester, 250 sqm, steel/blockwork, flat metal roofs, vandalised, yard breakout, drainage removal, development plot clearance—and send a fixed-price quote by lunchtime."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/ai-whatsapp/"
  tradePageUrl="/demolition-contractors/ai-receptionist/"
  ctaHeadline="Respond to the Social Club Demolition Photos While You Pulverise the RC Beams"
  ctaSubhead={`A developer sends six photos of a 600 sqm social club with a ten-week piling deadline. The AI responds while you crunch the concrete. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
/>
